{"description":"MIC is a rare example of someone who pushes culture forward while getting the day-to-day done. Always on the ground, he leads substantive discussions, explains complex topics clearly, and carefully onboards people from web2 to the chain. data.metadata: {"description":"I’ve known Pavil through the Pudgy/Abstract community since early 2024. What sets him apart is not only his style but his process. He starts with a short brief, quickly sends pencil sketches, agrees on a color palette, and then executes cleanly either on stream or offline.\nI first noticed him during live graffiti sessions on the Abstract portal: he turned multiple PFPs into cohesive, wall-ready compositions instead of just copying avatars. Later, at a local Pudgy meetup, he handled a live painting segment with clear preparation, no delays, and strong composition, and attendees ended up using the artwork as social headers.\nHis contribution to the community is real: he regularly supports Pudgy Russia, helps creators with custom pieces, and communicates professionally (fast replies, realistic timelines, no drama). If you need someone who delivers striking graffiti and represents the culture responsibly, Pavil is reliable and easy to recommend."}

translation.translatedDescription:
I’ve known Pavil through the Pudgy/Abstract community since early 2024. What sets him apart is not only his style but his process. He starts with a short brief, quickly sends pencil sketches, agrees on a color palette, and then executes cleanly either on stream or offline.
I first noticed him during live graffiti sessions on the Abstract portal: he turned multiple PFPs into cohesive, wall-ready compositions instead of just copying avatars. Later, at a local Pudgy meetup, he handled a live painting segment with clear preparation, no delays, and strong composition, and attendees ended up using the artwork as social headers.
His contribution to the community is real: he regularly supports Pudgy Russia, helps creators with custom pieces, and communicates professionally (fast replies, realistic timelines, no drama). If you need someone who delivers striking graffiti and represents the culture responsibly, Pavil is reliable and easy to recommend.
